      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 67,
      "message": "Changing the `periodSeconds` will cause the liveness probe to be executed only every two minutes. Accordingly, a broken container will only be restarted after that time. \nEdit: ~~If the motivation is to account for a long startup time of the container, then please consider using a [startupProbe](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/configure-liveness-readiness-startup-probes/#define-startup-probes)~~. Changing the `periodSeconds` is not a good idea imho.",
      "author": {
