    {
      "id": "3eb4d7d4_3b2bb70d",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dmaap/components/message-router/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 67,
      "message": "The reason for having periodSeconds to 120 was that message-router does not allow client to poll for events 'too frequently'. If done so, it returns \"429- Too many requests\" error response. Current check is for TCP socket, hence it didn't matter.\n\nTesting shows that the value can be reduced to 30 seconds, will change accordingly.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8242,
        "name": "Kedar Ambekar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kedar.ambekar@t-systems.com",
        "username": "kedar.t"
      },
      "updated": "2023-08-25 10:10:37.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "a470e94c_ccb1e682",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "50bd5720_ec070c8c",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dmaap/components/message-router/templates/statefulset.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 38,
      "message": "This is the default behaviour of message router. It means the clients are polling too frequently and should reduce accordingly.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4405,
        "name": "Fiachra Corcoran",
        "display_name": "Fiachra Corcoran (EST)",
        "email": "fiachra.corcoran@est.tech",
        "username": "efiacor"
      },
      "updated": "2023-09-01 07:19:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "6ff26fc9_fc51453e",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "29bb0340_1f1ae060",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dmaap/components/message-router/templates/statefulset.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 38,
      "message": "The case when 503 is returned when clients are polling too frequently is understood and agree that it is default behaviour.\n\nThere is another case when 503 is returned as well. That 503 response contains \"KafkaConsumerCacheException: The cache service is unavailable.\" Such 503 response is returned to ALL clients irrespective of the polling frequency. This condition occurs when pod is running for few days and it requires to re-create the pod.\n\nThat's why suggesting to have this change in livenessProbe to detect this error condition.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8242,
        "name": "Kedar Ambekar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kedar.ambekar@t-systems.com",
        "username": "kedar.t"
      },
      "updated": "2023-09-01 08:03:18.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "50bd5720_ec070c8c",
      "unresolved": true
    }
  ]
